```

So the picture is consistent: TE devs already know this is a real bug, they isolated it into its own multi-process script, and even that script isn't currently green in CI ("add this test back after it is verified"). When you say `pytest test_distributed_moe_block` doesn't hit this error, it's most likely because that test (a) doesn't exist in this checkout (no file matches `**/test*moe*` anywhere in the workspace) and/or (b) if it exists in your other branch, it's likely either (i) skipping the grouped_dense path or (ii) running on a system where someone is launching it through `multi_process_launch.sh`.

